  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The Örebro prevention program is a brief (6 x 30 minutes)program administered to parents of
      13-16 year old youths in regular parental meetings. The program aims to encourage parents to
      maintain a restrictive attitude towards youth drinking throughout their children's teenage
      years, and thereby postpone and reduce youth drinking. A previous quasi-experimental study by
      the program developers showed a sustained alcohol-specific restrictivity among parents
      exposed to the program, and also a reduction on drinking measures among the youths of the
      exposed parents (Koutakis, Stattin &amp; Kerr, 2008). This study aims to investigate whether
      these effects are sustained also when the program has gone into wide dissemination in Sweden.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
